# Introduction

Thanks for your interest in contributing to the "Deciphering compound rain-on-snow flood pathways as observed from satellites" research project. Collaborations and one-off contributions are most welcome here!

# How to Contribute

At this time, the best way to contribute is as follows:

1. Preferably, chat with Vincenzo about the contribution. He's the lead researcher of this project and would love to hear from you. You can do this by creating an Issue if you'd like.
2. Make changes on a branch (or a fork), and when ready, create a Pull Request so that changes can be reviewed.

Please be kind; we adopt the Contributor Covenant [code of conduct](CODE_OF_CONDUCT).